| Code    | Meaning               | Use Case Example                        |
| ------- | --------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **200** | OK                    | âœ… Request succeeded (GET, PUT, DELETE)  |
| **201** | Created               | âœ… New resource created (POST)           |
| **204** | No Content            | âœ… Success but no data returned (DELETE) |
| **400** | Bad Request           | âŒ Invalid input from client             |
| **401** | Unauthorized          | âŒ Missing or invalid auth credentials   |
| **403** | Forbidden             | âŒ Authenticated but access denied       |
| **404** | Not Found             | âŒ Resource not found                    |
| **409** | Conflict              | âŒ Duplicate or conflicting request      |
| **500** | Internal Server Error | âŒ Server-side failure                   |



### ğŸ”§ Backend API Expectations

Your Spring Boot backend should expose:

* `GET /api/notes` â†’ returns all notes as JSON
* `POST /api/notes` â†’ accepts `{ content: "" }`
* `PUT /api/notes/{id}` â†’ update a note
* `DELETE /api/notes/{id}` â†’ delete a note

